Frontend Unit Tests (Vitest + RTL)

This is an isolated test project that imports the app component from `../../frontend/src`. It avoids modifying your existing app‚Äôs package.json.

Setup
- From this folder, install deps: `npm install` 
- Run tests: `npm test` (headless) or `npm run test:ui` (watch/UI)

What‚Äôs covered
- Loads and renders messages list (status text ‚ÄúShowing 1 message.‚Ä?
- Rejects empty message submission (shows validation error)
- Submits a new message and refreshes list (POST called, content appears)
- File upload: error without file; success with file (shows ‚ÄúUploaded pic.png‚Ä?
- WebSocket notification increments unread (shows ‚ÄúUnread: 1‚Ä?

Key expectations (assertions)
- Loading state is visible before fetch resolves
- After fetch, a message item text appears
- Empty submit shows ‚ÄúMessage cannot be empty‚Ä?- POST /api/messages/ is called when submitting valid content
- Upload without selecting file shows ‚ÄúPlease choose a file to upload.‚Ä?- Successful upload shows ‚ÄúUploaded <filename>‚Ä?- After a mocked WS notification, unread counter becomes 1

Notes
- Tests stub global `fetch` and provide a mock `WebSocket`
- If CSS import causes issues, Vitest config enables CSS handling via Vite
